    <div class="text-center">
        <h1>Welcome to your Bug Inspector!</h1>
        <p class="fs-2">
            Every Company has a goal and a way to achieve that goal. The
            Bug Inspector will help you achieve your goals. Here you
            can make large goals that you want to accomplish for your company in the
            form of Projects. Those Projects can then be filled with small steps needed to
            accomplish that project in the form of tickets. There is a lot that the Bug Inpsector
            can do for you to simplify projects and accoplish goals. Give it a try today as a Demo User!
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/Account/Login">
            Demo User Sign In
        </a>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-cols-2 mt-5 g-5">
        <div class="col">
            <!-- Primary background on hover -->
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm card-hover card-hover-primary h-100 w-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Admin Management</h5>
                    <p class="card-text fs-sm">
                        The Bug Inspector will allow someone that is an Admin the ability to
                        monitor all parts of the company. This will allow for them to edit the
                        company page, or a project, or even a ticket. The Admin has easy control
                        over everything that a Company may run into and will be able to get things done fast
                        and easily.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <!-- Primary background on hover -->
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm card-hover card-hover-primary h-100 w-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Project Details</h5>
                    <p class="card-text fs-sm">
                        One of the most important parts to any company is the projects they are working on.
                        On this page you will be able to see every needed detail that a project has. You will
                        be able to see the tickets that are paired with that project, and how it is coming along
                        on its deadline. If you are in the proper role, you can even make edits to the project
                        as is neccessary to keep everything moving at a good pace.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <!-- Primary background on hover -->
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm card-hover card-hover-primary h-100 w-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Ticket Creation</h5>
                    <p class="card-text fs-sm">
                        The Bug Inspector makes it very simple to add a ticket that belongs to a project.
                        It can be made by anyone for any project that they are working on or have been assigned to
                        and regardless of your role it is simple to go back and edit the ticket to make sure that
                        everything is running smoothly for each and every project.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <!-- Primary background on hover -->
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm card-hover card-hover-primary h-100 w-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Ticket Details</h5>
                    <p class="card-text fs-sm">
                        Now for one of the most important points of the projects, it's tickets.
                        These are bite-sized steps that are a part of the project and just as you can do with
                        projects you can also see all of the details for each individual ticket. If you are
                        in the proper role you can also add comments to the ticket for extra clarity or to report on
                        the steps being taken to move the ticket along. You can also add downloadable attachments
                        that can be useful for anyone working on the ticket.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
